dialogue.speaker: Unknown
dialogue.text: I'm Mother Nature, wise guy, and I don't remember asking you to shuffle my dead twigs around.

dialogue.speaker: Dilbert
dialogue.text: Uh-oh, gosh, I was just trying to tidy up a bit for spring.

dialogue.speaker: Unknown
dialogue.text: Are you saying you don't like my housekeeping?

dialogue.speaker: Unknown
dialogue.text: That's it. No dinner for you tonight, and I'm sending locusts to eat your house.
